# Naming

## Purpose

Predictable names reduce AI search errors and review friction.

## When It Applies

New files, packages, components, types, and Git branches.

## Requirements

| Kind | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Packages | `@repo/{name}` lowercase | `@repo/ui`, `@repo/core` |
| React components | PascalCase file + export | `ThemeToggle.tsx` |
| Hooks | `use` prefix, camelCase | `use-theme.ts` |
| Utils | camelCase functions | `formatRelativeTime` |
| Types | PascalCase | `User`, `ApiResponse` |
| API routes | kebab-case folders | `app/api/health/route.ts` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `APP_NAME` |
| Services | `{Entity}Service` | `UserService` |
| Repositories | `{Entity}Repository` | `SupabaseUserRepository` |

## Examples

```
packages/ui/src/components/empty-state.tsx   → EmptyState
packages/core/src/errors/index.ts            → ValidationError
docs/BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE.md                 → kebab in paths, SCREAMING for doc types
```

## Bad Examples

```
utils2.ts, helperFunctions.ts, data.ts
SupabaseStuff, user_service, APIHandler
mixing camelCase and snake_case in same module
```
